VirtLocalLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

VirtLocalLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement

VirtLocalLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a 32-bit identifier in IP address format; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

VirtLocalLsdbNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the virtual neighbor.

VirtLocalLsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

VirtLocalLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer.  It starts with the value '80000001'h

VirtLocalLsdbTransitArea.description: The transit area that the virtual link traverses.  By definition

VirtLocalLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.
